            },
            {
                "img": "https://arxiv.org/html/2605.13740/2605.13740v1/x24.png",
                "caption": "Figure 11:Prompt-information ablation.Average episode reward as the natural-language prompt is varied from no task description (L0) to the full description used in main experiments (L3). Performance is task dependent, indicating thatPinductorcombines LLM priors with trajectory feedback and benefits from structural task cues when the prior alone is underspecified.",
                "position": 2263
            },
